social_posts.post_text:
Happy first day of Advent!  Swapped out our hallway light for a candelabra with 24 packages tied up with string. 

The girls have already spotted number 1 for after school.  As always the activity will be to ‘write a letter to Santa’ to ensure I have enough time to get that one special gift under the tree.  What’s on yours today?!

Claire bear asked for a polar bear cake this year!  Lots of piped fur to match her unpredictable unruly curls. 🤍 She’s always been the most affectionate but very quick to physically defend her big sisters when someone is picking on them.  She will be the person to speak up for those who can’t, and we absolutely love that about her!  Extremely opinionated and stubborn…. It takes her the longest to get ready for school in the morning because she can’t be bothered with pants..or socks..or shoes….basically everything is a process that we haven’t quite figured out how to speed up yet.  She’s already starting to read small words and adores her classmates. 

Heartbroken to know she’s no longer a toddler, excited to see what this year brings.  Happy 4th birthday sweet girl! ✨

A few holiday decorations in the nick of time. 
Happy we were able to finish this little space for Edith just in time for Christmas.  Anyone else still decorating for the holiday or are you ready?

Haven’t posted in over a month after some much needed time to take care of all the colds/fevers/general fatigue around here!  Hopefully this winter has been easier for y’all. 🤍. 

Good news is we finally finished this little baking pantry so we’re back on track for the kitchen plans.  Thanks for sticking around; there’s lots more little DIYs to share this spring and our reno plans for 2023! 

Cabinet inspo: @thelonegooseco

A little afternoon calm in Edie’s room.  I added one of @loloirugs x @riflepaperco ‘s new rugs to her space (grove/khaki MAO-07) for a bit of spring despite the groundhog’s prediction of another 6 weeks of winter!  Love the whimsy of this collab and how it compliments the details in her bed.  Linking in stories along with 2 accent pillows that are worth a look. 🤍 #loloixriflepaperco #riflepapercoxloloi

How long did it take to make 50+ of these sweet Valentines?
Not berry long. 🍓 
.
The girls and I had fun cutting and lacing these for their classmates and joking to be gentle so we wouldn’t be handing out jam!  We adapted them from @vssmxncia who shared a smaller gift tag version.  With a larger scale and a few modifications a bag of strawberry fruit snacks fit perfectly!

A Frankenstein little diy desk this weekend. 🤍If you’ve ever made a piece of furniture you know new legs can be pricey (sometimes to the point where diy is unaffordable and hard to justify)!

Swipe to see where we sourced the legs for this longer desk.  Per usual…Marketplace!  The inside of the old piece was damaged so it worked out perfectly. 👏🏻👏🏻. Sharing more of this Frankenstein tomorrow. 🤍

A desk that sounds as wonderful as it looks. 👏🏻. When Edie asked to start piano lessons 6 months ago, we researched keyboards and figured we would just get an old table to set it on.  The dimensions were fairly hard to find though (long and narrow limited us to console tables) so we decided to start from scratch with a twist! 

Could you tell what was hidden in the faux drawer? 🎹

Shared sister space sunshine ☀️. I pulled the trigger on a dresser I shared in stories for the other side of the canopy bed yesterday.  Can’t wait for it to arrive and hopefully convince the half of you that voted to pass on it. 🤞🏻😅. Wish us luck!

Daylight saving hit like a ton of bricks this morning and I’m looking forward to bedtime already. 🙌🏻. Made a couple of changes in our bedroom including the new cutie plant (RIP olive tree) and this rich deep rug. 
It’s from the new Magnolia x Loloi collection (colorway SIN-01 pebble taupe) and the best part is that it’s machine washable and soft as butter. 🤍. Linking in stories #joannagainesxloloi

A first glimpse at Ben’s big kid room.  I’ve been wanting to try this little print diy for a while and found the perfect corner. 🤍. 

Tips on giving prints the illusion of paint can be as simple as textured paper, but if you’re looking for something more realistic try a coat of Mod Podge.  It gives a slight shine and extra character depending on how thick it’s applied. 🙌🏻. Love how easy it was, have you tried any of these tips before?

Make a wish sweet girl!🤍🦋. 

Our little Edith has grown so much this year.  Her confidence continues to soar as she learns to articulate what she enjoys; from writing and drawing, to play dates with her close group of girl friends. 
She’s often reserved when she get home from school but opens up and shares all the sweet things on her mind if you sit quietly with her long enough. 🤍. She asked for piano lessons this year and its made us so proud to watch her practice and try, even if she yells that she doesn’t know the finger position for half the songs (beats me either kiddo 🥴). 
Happy 7th birthday sweetheart, love you lots. xoxo.
